rlm-bq-archive

Multi-select BigQuery tables from the bq-open cache, run three
diagnostic queries per table (recent jobs, audit-log access, storage
freshness), print the results, ask for confirmation, then copy the
selected table(s) into the archival_data dataset with
`bq cp --no-clobber`.

Selected entries are first classified via `bq show`. Anything whose
type is VIEW or MATERIALIZED_VIEW is dropped from the run with a
"views do not need to be archived" notice — the diagnostics and copy
only operate on actual tables (TABLE / EXTERNAL / SNAPSHOT).

The original tables are NOT deleted. A `DROP TABLE` SQL block (plus
`bq rm` equivalents and queries to locate downstream views and
routines) is printed to stdout AND written to a timestamped file
under $TMPDIR/bq-archive-drop-<timestamp>.sql so the user can run
them later by hand.

The picker reuses the `~/.cache/bq-open/` cache — run `bq-open` once
first to populate it. The cache key is derived from BQ_SEARCH_PATH +
SANDBOX_BQ_PROJECT + SANDBOX_BQ_DATASETS (the same algorithm
rlm-bq-open uses), so changes to those env vars bust the cache for
both tools at once.

Key bindings:
  TAB / Shift-TAB  toggle selection
  Ctrl-P           cycle preview height (tall -> short -> hidden)
  Enter            confirm selection and proceed to diagnostics

Confirmation requires typing 'yes' before any copy happens.

ENVIRONMENT
  BQ_SEARCH_PATH
      Required. Colon-separated GCP project IDs; same as bq-open.

  BQ_ARCHIVE_QUERY_PROJECT
      Optional. GCP project where the three diagnostic queries run
      (must have region-eu INFORMATION_SCHEMA.JOBS, .TABLES,
      .TABLE_STORAGE, and a bq_log.cloudaudit_googleapis_com_data_access
      table). Default: the source project of the selected table.

  BQ_ARCHIVE_TARGET
      Optional. project.dataset to which the archive copies are
      written. Default: <source_project>.archival_data.

  BQ_ARCHIVE_LOOKBACK_DAYS
      Optional. Interval (in days) for the JOBS + audit queries.
      Default: 7.

  BQ_ARCHIVE_IGNORED_PRINCIPALS
      Optional, colon-separated audit-log principals excluded from
      Query B (typically scheduled-job service accounts whose hits
      are noise). Default: composer@... and data-build-tool@...
      service accounts in storytel-data-platform-prod.

REQUIRES
  bq, fzf, jq
